Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:16.49,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(642,604)}Episode 5
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(664,444)}Ten: Tenho-doori no Kaidanji\N(The Nice Guy on Tenho Way)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.32,0:05:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What round it it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,South Hand 4, last round
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy from Tokyo is in 3rd
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.92,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,3rd place?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But his last hand is good
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.62,0:05:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the sort of hand that could pull off a sudden reversal if it gets big
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.12,0:06:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Honiisou, ShoSan with one dora. A Baiman hand that can put him on top
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.32,0:06:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's bold he can discard a 3/6/9 for a single wait on Red Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Later he could draw a Red dragon for a 3rd turn as dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore this guy's going for Chitoitsu (all pairs hand).\N A previously undiscarded tile like Red Dragon could be dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.40,0:06:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.52,0:06:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,6,400 points
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.82,0:06:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, darn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.95,0:06:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so waiting on Red Dragon, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.97,0:06:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-you two KNOW each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.07,0:06:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A little
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.18,0:07:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,o-okay
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.79,0:07:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.55,0:07:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you lost on purpose, didn't you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.57,0:07:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no reason for you to discard the Red Dragon there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Leave it to you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.48,0:07:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to show them my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,my skill, yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.37,0:07:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but also my luck
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to show them... my game flow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So THAT'S the number one guy on the East team?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.62,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll be a blowout for the West team won't it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,HOLD ON NOW
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.25,0:07:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn over Ten's subsequent draws from the point he lost
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.07,0:08:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,y-yessir
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.27,0:08:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A Red Dragon, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.77,0:08:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.52,0:08:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but, how?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You lot couldn't possibly understand, but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that guy could SENSE there was a Red Dragon coming
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought the Eastern head was pure trash,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.38,0:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it don't look like that at all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're late
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The 3rd member of the East team
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.67,0:08:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(612.445,81.555)}Asai "Ganpai" Ginji
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:58.35,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(389.333,560.667)}Ganpai: (lit. "wounded tile") is the cheat of marking tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:55.75,Default - top,,0,0,0,,A most valued artisan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.75,0:08:59.07,Default - top,,0,0,0,,through which almost no opponent can see
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.07,0:09:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,His skill at handling tiles is near that of an acrobat
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened? We still need one man for the East team?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.62,0:09:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.42,0:09:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A notable ringer took the cash and simply vanished
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,burns me the fuck up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.32,0:09:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt this contest is gonna be tough to win
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.17,0:09:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked, but couldn't get him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.81,0:09:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Breh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.74,0:09:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.37,0:09:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's no good for the East team
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.48,0:09:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.63,0:09:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to wash your hands of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.70,0:09:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is no place for a normie like you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least he's got the game
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.37,0:09:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and some spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.28,0:10:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just try me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for as far as you can use me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For two long years I've been restless
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.87,0:10:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.67,0:10:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and so
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.77,0:10:12.97,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,NO
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight your battles in the normie world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.25,0:10:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It... suits you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid, how old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.67,0:10:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,27
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.62,0:10:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Rash, brash...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.62,0:10:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,reckless
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.62,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a good look bout him, doesn't he
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks just like you did, Ten. Long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.62,0:10:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our opponents won't be expecting a greenhorn like this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.48,0:10:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He might just be our... trump card
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.32,0:10:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Put him in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:15.10,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(888,453.111)}通天閣\NTsū-TEN-kaku
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.19,0:11:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The West team roster
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.49,0:11:48.09,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(946.667,702)}Harada Katsumi\NMitsui Jyuuji\NAkutsu Tetsu\N{\b1}Soga Mitsui{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.83,0:12:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.83,0:12:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga's name is here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.49,0:12:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Those West bastards
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.33,0:12:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They even pulled Soga into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.73,0:12:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A master who controlled the underworld for years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a ten year period he didn't lose once
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I heard he retied because of poor health
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.68,0:12:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My god. To think even Soga is here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First, there is a proposal from the West team
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.08,0:12:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What if both teams
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.08,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on top of normal Mahjong rules
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,attach a single additional condition
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.68,0:12:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as you prefer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The East team players
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.39,0:13:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,here you are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.33,0:13:18.43,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(666.667,235.333)}Ten Takashi\NAsai Ginji\NIsokaze Ken\NIgawa Hiroyuki
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.66,0:13:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The East team looks useless
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.18,0:13:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten's the only smart one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.66,0:13:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like the East team could get Akagi
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we went to great pains to get Soga...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.18,0:13:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's looking like it's going to be a dull match
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.30,0:13:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be time momentarily.\NPlease proceed to the contest area
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:46.92,Default - top - cyan,,0,0,0,,A Fukumoto Nobuyuki appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.33,0:13:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.80,0:14:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a time restriction rule
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.05,0:14:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone caught cheating hands over his point box
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.95,0:14:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the 8 people here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.95,0:14:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,only four will advance to the final round
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.98,0:14:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And our proposed additional rule
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.45,0:14:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan-Shibari
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.45,0:14:38.05,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(648,136.667)}Mangan-Shibari (満貫縛り): A rule restricting winning hands to Mangan or higher. No "trivial" wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.45,0:14:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wins less than Mangan are just useless
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no penalty for not achieving Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.88,0:14:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a rule eliminating accumulated wins?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.90,0:14:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.71,0:15:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally points go to the winner
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, the points of someone who wins a hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would absolutely never increase
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This rule...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ensures an upset is always possible with a single direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.15,0:15:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If points don't increase someone with no points can't recover
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you deal into someone's hand, it instantly starts a countdown to death
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.10,0:15:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We accept
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:04.45,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,East Hand 1
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,F-fast\NOn only the 3rd turn
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.10,0:16:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with a Mangan-shibari?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.38,0:17:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a risky discard
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.65,0:17:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, seeing discards like that, it on the contrary makes me SUSPICIOUS of Sou (bamboo) tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.85,0:17:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I guess other tiles are okay, but I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This Riichi is meant to measure the skill of these two
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Or to put it another way,\Nto find which is an easy mark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at the bias in his discards
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.10,0:17:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone would have a bad feeling about Sou tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken went with his gut feeling, as he's the type that acts on hunches
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki is the type that places logic as a priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.54,0:18:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll follow theory in this situation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.84,0:18:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'll certainly play the appropriate safe tile, BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that normal style of playing is the worst here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on Mitsui's discards, I've got the 4th and last 2 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.84,0:18:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,this OUGHT to pass here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.57,0:18:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one Ura-dora of two
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.50,0:19:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.74,0:19:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to fall for a hackneyed trap like this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.39,0:19:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not worth talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.75,0:19:34.91,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,East Hand 3
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.15,0:19:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,s-sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he's missing a tile!\NHe's only got 12!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in Shohai. What an incompetent mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:07.00,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,75.333)}Shōhai(少牌): Having too few tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.90,0:21:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Izzat a 1 Pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.86,0:21:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,RON
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.00,0:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou (4 concealed triplets)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's no longer in Shohai!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.16,0:21:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,H-he's done the UNTHINKABLE
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.70,0:21:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the rules of Mahjong, that one known as Shohai is a peculiarly odd
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.15,0:21:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,While it's clearly a foul, you can't stop the game for it. Only disregard a win
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.86,0:21:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's my advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.86,0:22:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm in Shohai, no one pays me any attention
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.85,0:22:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought I could take down Harada with a clean game
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.25,0:22:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's needed is for him to see I have the full 13 tiles when I reveal my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.65,0:22:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall before me has an East wind on the end
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.25,0:22:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Only I saw it when I knocked it over before
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.10,0:22:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so, putting the East wind and 6 Sou from the wall in my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.50,0:22:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can pull the 1 Pin Harada discarded on the first turn
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.00,0:22:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the 1 Pin and switch it out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can pull an East wind and 1 Pin into my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.95,0:22:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,completing my SuuAnKou single tile wait
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.36,0:22:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains to to RON Harada on his 1 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.55,0:22:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.85,0:22:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,47,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.70,0:22:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest is over
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.70,0:22:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,H-harada dealt into a dealer Yakuman!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.30,0:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.30,0:22:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take us for fools
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That wall in front of you went from 9 tiles to 8 tiles wide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.15,0:23:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious you pulled two tiles from that wall
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.35,0:23:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the hell you on about m8?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.35,0:23:14.35,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,YOU FUCKER!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.00,0:23:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsui
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.35,0:23:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,just be quiet a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,BUT
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.40,0:23:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone is going to fight over this, it's me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll SETTLE IT
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.00,0:23:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're called "Ken" aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.50,0:23:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to remember your name
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.15,0:23:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken clearly pulled two tiles from his wall
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.85,0:23:48.90,Default - top,,0,0,0,,And he's still got ONE IN HIS HAND
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.90,0:23:51.55,Default - top,,0,0,0,,What's he going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.55,0:23:53.55,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Cut away man
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:23:58.90,Default - top,,0,0,0,,But if there's no tile in that hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.90,0:24:02.20,Default - top,,0,0,0,,with that cut you only confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.20,0:24:05.85,Default - top,,0,0,0,,YOU LOSE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.60,0:24:11.16,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Do you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.16,0:24:14.60,Default - top,,0,0,0,,When someone dies from a gunshot wound
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:16.60,Default - top,,0,0,0,,they die senseless, in shock
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.60,0:24:18.60,Default - top,,0,0,0,,however...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.60,0:24:22.53,Default - top,,0,0,0,,death by stabbing is a LOT more painful
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.53,0:24:24.53,Default - top - cyan,,0,0,0,,w-what are you saying？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.56,0:24:26.60,Default - top,,0,0,0,,This Mahjong is a scramble over life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.60,0:24:31.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,If I confirm my opponent is cheating I take his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.10,0:24:33.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,and I'll do so at my leisure
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.10,0:24:35.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,AT AN AUTOPSY
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.10,0:24:37.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,S-STOP PLEASE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.05,0:24:43.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,Too late
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.10,0:24:45.10,Default - top,,0,0,0,,HA HA HA HA
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:09.11,Default - white - top,,0,0,0,,Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.90,0:25:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This man kills without qualm
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.10,0:25:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.96,0:25:04.96,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd mix it up a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.66,0:25:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us confirm your two players
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.23,0:25:07.23,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,My short sword will taste blood
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.40,0:25:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki is cornered\NIt's over
